# UI layer boundaries

Canonical write-up: **`docs/coding-guidebook.md`** §2–3. Copy bags: **`i11n-colocation.mdc`**.

## Dependency direction

```text
page.tsx → feature (src/app/**/components) → src/ui (shell + primitives) → theme
```

Never import upward from primitives into features. Inside `src/ui/**`, import siblings **relatively** (not `@ui`) to avoid barrel cycles.

## `src/ui/<Name>/` folder shape

Every shared UI module is a **folder** next to siblings:

```text
src/ui/<Name>/
  <Name>.tsx          # main export
  i11n.json           # when the module owns user-facing copy
  <Name>.stories.tsx  # title: ui/<Name>
  index.ts            # public exports
  # optional helpers / subcomponents in the same folder
```

Import as `@/ui/<Name>` or from `@ui` after `bun run exports-gen`.

## Two kinds of modules in `src/ui`

### Primitives (presentational)

- Atoms/molecules reusable on any route (Button, Input, Card, Avatar, Drawer, …).
- **No** Apollo hooks, **no** `useUserStore`, **no** pathname branching for chrome.
- No marketplace-scoped defaults; compose `SpotIllustration` + local Stack in features.
- No domain status enums — feature adapters compose `Badge`.
- If Apollo / cookie / Me wiring is needed, keep a **thin adapter outside** `src/ui` (example: presentational `src/ui/LanguageSwitcher` + connected `src/i18n/LanguageSwitcher.tsx`).

### Shell chrome (app-aware)

- Cross-route chrome: **`Header`**, **`Dock`** (menus, notifications drawer, dock rail).
- May read Me / notifications / routes / Apollo.
- Still live under `src/ui/<Name>/` with colocated `i11n.json`.
- Stories: `ui/Header`, `ui/Dock` (same ownership title rule as other `@ui` modules).
- May import from `@/app/**` only when wiring shell behavior (exception to the primitive rule).

## `src/app` — features

- Route sections, mappers (`helpers/`), providers (`context/`), GraphQL.
- Thin adapters that wire store/context into `@ui` when the primitive is data-agnostic.
- Domain cards stay presentational; one entity + view/state — no per-route card forks.

## Checklist

- [ ] New shared control → `src/ui/<Name>/` with `ui/<Name>` story, or extend an existing primitive.
- [ ] Shell chrome → `src/ui/Header` / `src/ui/Dock` (not a separate `src/components` tree).
- [ ] User-facing copy → colocated `i11n.json` + `useI11n(bag)` (see **`i11n-colocation.mdc`**).
- [ ] Route UI → colocated `components/` next to `page.tsx`.
- [ ] Primitives do not import `@/app/**`; shell chrome may.
- [ ] Inside `src/ui/**`, relative sibling imports only — not `@ui`.
